All the comments here defending this is mad. If someone is smashing shit and kicking etc. That is violence, that is aggression.

You cannot speculate that he wouldnt do X, Y or Z. Or that because he is doing what we see that this means he wouldnt do X, Y or Z. That is horseshit.

From this video what we KNOW is he doesnt have qualms behaving this way.

comment:
"No one will believe that I made this all up. No one will believe that you are a victim." -- shAmber Turd.

This doesn't feel like a victim trying to film their abuser. I've been through abusive relationships and I'll be honest, his behavior -- slamming the cupboards, kicking the fridge, the breaking glass -- did make me very uncomfortable. I'm not even in the room and I flinched to a lot of it. It waay triggered my fight or flight.

But whenever that happens, I leave. I get very small, very quiet, and I find a way to leave the situation as quickly and quietly as I can. I jump and flinch at every word and slam. I scuttle away if they come near me. I disengage any convo, do not make eye contact, and apologize.

She is not frightened of him or his behavior. Shes not startled by the bangs or him kicking the fridge. She doesnt flinch away when he comes near her or starts yelling. She actually seems to be antagonizing him. "What happened this morning. What happened? Why are you so upset?" And "did you drink that all today?"

And didn't she allege that he beat her up after finding the phone? But he just left  

Also, did you hear her giggle near the end when she picks up the phone?

comment:
She loves it when Johnny Depp is angry and hurt. The way she is provoking him by not acknowledging his pain. "You were so sweet this morning" and "we didn`t even have a fight", is her way of trying to turn his anger and frustration on her and their relationship, to make it seem like this is about her.
I don`t know why Johnny is angry, I have read some stuff, but what do I know. But it was obviously something that made him mad. But Amber was not worried for him. She didn`t ask what was wrong because she was worried about him, she asked because she wanted to put herself into the situation and make it about her and their relationship. Or make it seem like it was.
Not for one second was she worried for her safety. Not even when it was alcohol involved and he was drunk. She even laughed at the end there.

And Johnny Depp never touched her, or even indicated that he would hurt her. Not even after he saw she was fucking filming him. He threw the camera away and left the room. I personally think he had every right to do that.
Destroying all the other stuff makes many people uncomfterbole, I included. But sometimes people just need to get that anger out, and destroying shit is a good and relatively healthy way to get all that energy out so that you can think more clearly later.
That was most likely his stuff as well. No matter how uncomfterbole that made me, I have no right in judging Johnny for destroying his own things in his own house while Turd is secretly filming his mental breakdown.

I`m sorry I watched this. It should not have been in the public.

comment: Jesus, the entire comment section is filled with idiots, woman haters and liars... SO JUST TO CLARIFY: This video was recorded on February 11th, the morning before he recorded a performance with his band for the Grammy's and was involved in a photo session to promote it.  Johnny's mother did NOT just die.  She died months later on May 20th. Johnny had NOT just found out about having financial problems, that occurred ~April 22. Furthermore, what you witnessed here IS by the US legal definition DOMESTIC VIOLENCE.  Any act of violence OR any threat of physical violence that is used to intimidate a person IS MISDEMEANOR DOMESTIC VIOLENCE.  According to California penal code, both parties must give their permission in order to be recorded UNLESS a person is recording a crime or expects to be recording a crime, such as an act of domestic violence, as we have seen here. Any person who is admonishing her for recording this, for attempting to obtain evidence of the abuse she has been suffering, should be ashamed of yourself ESPECIALLY, if you are purportedly here to "defend an abuse victim".  PLEASE EDUCATE YOURSELF ON DOMESTIC VIOLENCE... NOT HERE! GO DO SOME ACTUAL RESEARCH, BC MOST OF YOU SOUND REALLY FKN STUPID!!!

comment:
I don't know what to make of this. Everyone in the comments is saying his mom died, but if my mom died I wouldn't get drunk as F and break everything in my kitchen. Yes, he's swearing because he hurt his hand, but he hurt himself because he was belligerent and was slamming everything. So I mean, what did he think was going to happen? 

All the celebs that defend him say they couldn't possibly imagine Depp hurting a fly, yet here he is being violent and smashing a kitchen. While it is true that Depp did not physically touch Amber, it isn't a stretch to imagine him, in a drunken rage, throwing something at her. In addition, all abuse doesn't have to be physical. Can you imagine your spouse getting super drunk and smashing your kitchen? Imagine the nerves, tension, etc. The fear. Even so, Amber does come off as crazy, laughing at the end. Some people laugh when nervous to release tension. Or maybe she was sick of no one believing her-- maybe she's a vengeful person and was excited to finally have some kind of evidence against Depp. Look, I'm not saying she's entirely innocent, but to cancel her and pretend like Depp is an angel just because you liked him as Jack Sparrow isn't logical. Amber and Johnny are both a mess and perhaps both deserve punishment. From this video, though, Johnny deserves it more.

comment:
Ok. Even leaving out the fact she may or may not have hit him (she did lets be honest) the fact of the matter here is. When this angry what did he hit? Her or the cupboards? He didn't know she was filming, and abusers generally know they can get away with, yknow, abuse, because they've manipulated the victim. So why, despite not knowing of the camera, did he not attack her at all? Why did he do nothing to her UNTIL he saw the camera, which btw, would incite anger in anyone!! If you're pissed off about something and someone's sitting their recording you in a state of distress instead of offering help, what youre just gonna smile and laugh it off? No and don't even lie and say you would. AND THEN YEA he takes the phone and we can't see what happens, but we can hear. We never hear any contact or whimpers or cries or sounds of distress. Just the sound of a phone hitting the ground. No, abusive language, just a man getting rid of the device being used to record him in pain. He then walks away. 

Idk about you, but if I was casually abusing my spouse and found out she was recording me in a drunken rage, I wouldn't preserve the evidence. I wouldn't simply toss the phone to the side and storm off. Id smash the fucking phone, water log it, whatever it takes to destroy the footage permanently, and then, yknow... abuse! His actions are that of a man whose not having a good day, is pissed off, and whose wife is recording him like its a joke for the internet (little did he know it would be used in a defamation attempt.) Why would any abuser, who spots the device recording. Leave it intact. It makes LITERALLY 0 sense

comment:
Why this is not evidence in AH‚Äôs favor:

Amber:
- Doesn‚Äôt act like an abuse victim here, even as the person who she claims is her abuser is obviously very upset at the moment. She doesn‚Äôt seem worried about her safety, but more about JD being in view of the camera all the time. Had she been abused, she would in this situation be more concerned with getting out unharmed instead of keep filming him. 
- Afterwards she laughs.

Johnny:
- From what I‚Äôve heard, this is filmed soon after JD‚Äôs mother died, which gives him a very good reason for being in a foul mood, which gives him in return a good reason for being drunk.
- JD is very obviously drunk, and according to AH and her witnesses, this is the time he becomes ‚Äúthe monster‚Äù. But the only thing we see here is a very upset Johnny, who takes his anger our on inanimate objects, not on any person. Hitting stuff and people is very different things, and because you are capable of hitting things it doesn‚Äôt mean you‚Äôre capable of doing it to another person. Hitting stuff and people cannot be compared.
- He says, ‚Äúyou want to see crazy? Here‚Äôs your crazy,‚Äù or something similar, as he fills a glass of wine to the brim. This is already a crazy level for him. Throwing stuff and hitting people is not where he begins to think thing‚Äôs to be crazy, it‚Äôs where everyone‚Äôs lost their horses. Keep that in mind.
- JD doesn‚Äôt come near her until he discovers that she‚Äôs filming him. And even then he takes her phone, or whatever she‚Äôs using, and from what we hear, there‚Äôs nothing that hits her during the moment we can‚Äôt see anything. We only hear him calling her an ass and leaving the room.

JD hasn‚Äôt done anything violent towards her, while being the so called ‚Äúmonster‚Äù.

I think, over all, this speaks very badly about AH. She‚Äôs filming him during a very vulnerable and upset state, while he is oblivious to her doing so. I would think this is counting to be breaking the privacy laws or whatever. This video is contradicting her claims more than giving them credibility.
